    <abstract id="aspace_6952c857aabb1313002526f4115b0aef">Doris Tobias (d. 2009) was a food writer based in New York City. She worked as a food and wine columnist and editor for <emph render="italic">Women's Wear Daily</emph> and <emph render="italic">Wine &amp; Spirits Magazine</emph>. Tobias published several cook books and reviewed numerous restaurants during her career. This collection documents her professional career as a female writer involved in the food industry in New York City during the late 20th century. Materials include recipes, menus, print publications, clippings, food and wine event packets, business cards, financial and apartment contract records, writings, and a toy truck commemorating George Duboeuf's annual Beaujolais Nouveau.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_b7bc61c27e1c0541ed2240505d69bc5c">Materials are primarily in English.</langmaterial>
